FROM tomcat:latest
RUN cp -R  /usr/local/tomcat/webapps.dist/*  /usr/local/tomcat/webapps
COPY webapp/target/webapp.war /usr/local/tomcat/webapps



1) --- FROM tomcat:latest

This line sets the base image to the official latest version of Apache Tomcat, which comes preconfigured with all necessary dependencies for running Java web applications.

2) --RUN cp -R /usr/local/tomcat/webapps.dist/* /usr/local/tomcat/webapps

This command copies the default web applications provided in the Tomcat image from webapps.dist to the actual deployment directory webapps. 
Some Tomcat images keep default apps (like the manager app) in webapps.dist rather than webapps by default, so this step ensures the container will have them available when running.

3) --- COPY webapp/target/webapp.war /usr/local/tomcat/webapps

This line copies the built WAR file for the user's application from the Docker build context into the webapps directory inside the Tomcat container.
Placing the WAR here triggers Tomcat to automatically deploy the application upon startup, making it accessible at the configured context path.
